## 🏗️ Standard Service Code Structure

Tất cả services tuân theo cấu trúc NestJS module-based pattern:

```
packages/2-services/{service-name}/
├── src/
│   ├── main.ts                         # Service entry point (gRPC server)
│   ├── app.module.ts                   # Root module (imports all feature modules)
│   │
│   ├── 📁 modules/                     # Feature modules (domain-driven)
│   │   ├── 📁 {feature-name}/         # Each feature = one module
│   │   │   ├── {feature}.module.ts    # Module definition
│   │   │   ├── {feature}.service.ts   # Business logic
│   │   │   ├── {feature}.controller.ts # gRPC controller (optional, location varies)
│   │   │   └── dto/                   # Data Transfer Objects (optional)
│   │   │       └── *.dto.ts           # DTOs (import from 7-shared, not hard-coded)
│   │   │
│   │   └── ...                        # Other feature modules
│   │
│   ├── 📁 controllers/                 # gRPC Controllers (optional, some services)
│   │   └── {service}.controller.ts    # Main gRPC controller (community, monetization)
│   │
│   ├── 📁 grpc/                       # gRPC Controllers (optional, some services)
│   │   └── {service}.controller.ts    # gRPC controller (search-service)
│   │
│   ├── 📁 common/                     # Shared utilities
│   │   ├── database/                  # Database module (most services)
│   │   │   ├── database.module.ts
│   │   │   └── database.service.ts
│   │   ├── queue/                     # Event Bus queue (services with async communication)
│   │   │   ├── queue.module.ts
│   │   │   └── {service}-events.service.ts
│   │   └── cache/                     # Redis cache (services with caching)
│   │       └── cache.module.ts
│   │
│   ├── 📁 workers/                    # Event Bus workers (optional, some services)
│   │   ├── {feature}.worker.ts        # Worker processes
│   │   └── {feature}.consumer.ts      # Event consumers
│   │
│   ├── 📁 gateways/                   # WebSocket gateways (websocket-service only)
│   │   └── websocket.gateway.ts
│   │
│   ├── 📁 meilisearch/                # MeiliSearch client (search-service only)
│   │   └── meilisearch.service.ts
│   │
│   └── 📁 config/                     # Configuration
│       └── configuration.ts           # App, database, gRPC configs
│
├── database/                           # Prisma database layer (optional, some services)
│   ├── schema.prisma                  # Prisma schema (all entities)
│   └── migrations/                    # Database migrations
│
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── nest-cli.json
└── README.md
```

**Note:** Prisma schema location varies:
- Some services: `database/schema.prisma` (at root)
- Some services: `src/database/schema.prisma` (in src)
- Database access is always through `src/common/database/database.service.ts` (PrismaService)

### Controller Location Patterns

Controllers can be located in different places depending on the service:

- **In modules**: `src/modules/{feature}/{feature}.controller.ts` (users-service, stories-service, ai-service)
- **In controllers folder**: `src/controllers/{service}.controller.ts` (community-service, monetization-service)
- **In grpc folder**: `src/grpc/{service}.controller.ts` (search-service)

### Common Folder Patterns

- **`common/database/`**: Database module with Prisma (most services)
- **`common/queue/`**: Event Bus queue module (stories, search, websocket, notification services)
- **`common/cache/`**: Redis cache module (stories-service)

### Workers Folder

Services that consume events from Event Bus have a `workers/` folder:
- **search-service**: `workers/stories.consumer.ts`, `workers/social.consumer.ts`
- **websocket-service**: `workers/events.consumer.ts`, `workers/websocket.worker.ts`
- **notification-service**: `workers/comment-notification.worker.ts`, `workers/notification.worker.ts`

